rComments: He is most likely the worst teacher you will have in all of university. most of exam averages were failing. Might as well learn everything yourself in the book because he only has a few slides with a picture in each one and explains it like we all have our Ph. D, and it is a first year course. good luck

Don't take his class !! He talks WAY too fast, you get confused after literally 5 minutes. Make sure you buy the textbook because you will 100% be using it all the time. His midterm was so hard, and not just for me : the class average was 49%. Make sure to study EVERY LITTLE DETAILS if you want to at least pass the class. Good luck

He clearly knows what he's talking about but isn't the best at sharing that knowledge. He goes way too fast in his slides and doesn't have any words on the PowerPoint, only diagrams and pictures. He also does not tell you what specifically we need to know, just that everything is on the exam!
had to work a lot for it
Powerpoints were just pictures and he contradicted himself during his lectures. Would not take again. Try taking the class with someone else if you can!
No notes on powerpoints, talks incredibly fast

Renaud is not the best prof. You can tell he is very knowledgeable, but he talks fast in class and his powerpoints only have images. The anatomy book is a must for his part of the class as you have to use it to complete your notes. That being said go to class and try to take good notes. I also found his exam questions harder than the other profs.

- Interesting, dynamic and knowledgable prof however his powerpoint slides are incomplete and unfortunatly the textbook is not helpful for his part of ANP. However he is accessible outside of class hours and offers a Saturday "study class" before the exam which is helpful. ANP is a challenging but doable class, if you the work you will be fine.

Only information on PowerPoint slides were images with no words. Talks way to fast, all my notes were based on the textbook. Thank god I only had him for part of the semester because I wouldn't of passed. Multiple choice exam very tricky questions.

Slides contain no information just pictures and graphs. Speaks fast and goes through material quickly. Very hard to keep up with. If you miss information he says you're kinda screwed. Tests are very hard, specific questions. A lot of all the above are true/ false, gets very confusing. Avoid at all costs

there are no words on his powerpoints, just images, and he talks very fast so its extremely hard to type everything he says. half of my notes were incomplete. read the manual. every saturday before each of his exams, he does a "group thing" where his students can ask him questions and he answers them (about 3 hrs). this really helped so go if u can
No notes on the powerpoints, the test questions are so random, you need to understand everything when he's explaining something otherwise you're probably gonna fail unless you're a genius. GOOD LUCK!

His powerpoints only have pictures on them so if your're not in class, GOOD LUCK! He talks so fast that it makes writing notes hell. Exam questions are random and rarely studied. Probably the hardest class to take in first year and if you fail the first midterm don't worry the average is usually in the 50s
When I was in high school, my grades were always 80% and up. My first grade for my anatomy exam was a 44% (F) Well, good luck... I hope Jesus or whoever help you.

So basically this guy just gives u powerpoints with pictures on it then talks all class and he talks soo fast u barely have time to type everything hes saying so u for sure gotta read the manuel or else ur gonna fail. I didnt record cause i didnt feel like listening to him twice but u probs should

If you miss a second in class, you won't pass. Recording is a must if you can't type fast and studying is key. Exam questions are random and mostly ask for deduction even after hours of studying. Avoid class at all cost.

Possiblement le pire prof que j'ai jamais eu. Donne des powerpoint avec des images et aucunes explications ou notes et il est impossible de taper ce qu'il dit à la vitesse qu'il parle. Beaucoup de misère à étudier pour les examens car les notes sont toutes incomplètes. On doit se fier sur notre manuel qu'il dit est 15 ans en arrière de la science.

Overall not a great teacher. Doesn't have any words on slides, talks way too fast, to pass the class, it's better to read the book. I'd honestly rather get hit by a bus than to take another one of his classes.

Challenging ppts, but I actually like his method of teaching. I definately *understood*, rather than only learning by heart. I find his teaching entertaining (no monotone voice). He gave several hours of his time during weekends for a revision before the exams. He knows what he's talking about.

As others have said, the notes he gives are basically just images. You try to write stuff down but he speaks so fast, by the time you get home and read your notes they make no sense and are devoid of context.

Pour moi, less sections avec Dr Renaud ont été les plus difficiles puisqu'il va très vite et que ses PPT n'ont que des images et qu'il dit de ne pas se fier au manuel du cours, car il est plein d'erreur, mais il a fallut que je m'y fis quelques fois. Il a beaucoup de connaissances, mais va simplement trop rapidement pour des étudiants au bac!

Typing or writing your notes by hand ? Forget it. It's practically impossible with this guy. He talks way too fast and his PowerPoints contain neither words nor descriptions. By the end of his first week every student had brought in recorders and you might want to consider one as well. As a first year student, I would not recommend.

His slides had no words- he expected us to fill in all the information, but spoke very fast and didn't wear a mic. His exams were extremely difficult and specific. You have to rely heavily on the textbook; even then, the class average was 50%. He was enthusiastic about the subject matter, but the fact remains that his style doesn't suit 1st years.
Dans son ensemble très bon mais pas assez d'information dans ses présentations
His présentations are confusing and unclear. He talks so quickly that you can barely take notes properly. I REALLY dont recommend him!
Very stressful and confusing. Definitely would not recommend this prof if you're trying to make your parents proud.

Ses powerpoint contiennent juste des images, il parle trop vite et s'attend qu'on prenne en note tout ce qu'il dise. Il prend ses élèves pour des medecins et pense qu'ils ont les mêmes connaissances que lui. Ses examens sont très spécifiques. Je ne le recommande certainement pas!!!!!

By far the toughest prof yet. His exam is very specific and he contradicts himself a lot. He says not to use the textbook as the information in it is wrong. Speaks way too fast and it is hard to keep up. No words on slides (mostly pictures) so class is mandatory and even being present, it is very hard to do well. Class average was 58% for his exam.

He purposely removes notes off powerpoints so students show up to class and take it themselves. He speaks so fast and expects student to follow what he says and take notes at the same time. His midterms are very precise and pretty hard..I studied harder than I did in the first midterm and got a B (the textbook is what saved me).. avoid at all cost

Il n'était là que pour une section du cours, et une chance! Ce prof ne croit pas aux notes de cours. Ses powerpoints sont composés uniquement de photos. Il est donc nécessaire d'être présent à tous les cours.  Il parle très vite et des fois il se contredit. Son examen était difficile et certaines questions très précises.
